author: cbs8
title: Child reported injured at Jackson State homecoming parade
text:
JACKSON, Miss. (AP) - A child has been taken to a hospital in Jackson after an accident at the Jackson State University homecoming parade.
JSU spokesman L.A. Warren tells WLBT-TV ( http://bit.ly/1LtQ6yb ) that the accident happened Saturday morning when a little girl ran into the street for candy. The girl tripped on the pavement and her legs were struck by a float.
Warren said the girl, whose name and age were not available, was transported to a local hospital by ambulance.
Information from: WLBT-TV, http://www.wlbt.com
